<p><strong>Sources:</strong> The books <em>The X-Files Game: Prima&#8217;s Official Strategy Guide</em> by Rick Barba and <em>Writing for Interactive Media: The Complete Guide</em> by Jon Samsel and Darryl Wimberley. <em>Computer Gaming World</em> of June 1994, July 1994, February 1995, August 1998, and September 1998; <em>Edge</em> of January 2011; MacUser of December 1992; <em>CD-ROM Today</em> of August/September 1994; <em>InCider</em> of September 1991; <em>PC Games</em> of September 1998; <em>Extreme PlayStation</em> of August 1999 and September 1999. My thanks to reader Busca for digging up a few of these magazine sources for me!</p>
<p>Online sources include <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20070213044923/http://www.gamespot.com/pc/adventure/xfilesgame/review.html"><em>GameSpot&#8217;</em>s vintage review</a> of the game, <a href="http://www.hyperbole.com/full/attic/hbmag/index.html">the old HyperBole site</a>, <a href="http://storyslinger.com/">Greg Roach&#8217;s personal site</a>, <a href="https://spiritquesttours.com/">his Spirit Quest Tours site</a>, <a href="https://matadornetwork.com/bnt/interview-greg-roach-wants-you-to-make-a-spiritual-pilgrimage/">&#8220;Greg Roach Wants You to Make a Spiritual Pilgrimage&#8221;</a> by Christine Desadeleer at <em>Matador Network</em>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0yTO0fCtPlM">Roach being interviewed</a> by Dr. Sarah Larsen, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1IR2JQSiK-k">an old &#8220;making of&#8221; reel</a> for the game.</p>
<p><strong>Where to Get It: </strong><em>The X-Files Game</em> has never been re-released for digital purchase, doubtless due to the complications of licensing deals. The easiest way to play it today is to download <a href="https://collectionchamber.blogspot.com/2017/07/the-x-files-game.html">the pre-packaged version at <em>The Collection Chamber</em></a>.</p>
